<subSubSection id="C3606530B31E8A08FCDAFA34FBF6F9F0" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31E8A08FCDAFA34FBF6F9F0" blockId="13.[835,1437,1455,1981]" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FCDAFA34FC76FA49" box="[864,1007,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Distribution.</emphasis>
Found in the central Caribbean on St. Thomas, St. Jan and St. John (US Virgin Islands), Tortola and Virgen Gorda (British Virgin Islands), Isla Vieques just to the southeast of Puerto Rico, in eastern Cuba and on southern Hispaniola from 0-350 m in limestone and sandy areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
