</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3606530B31E8A0BFCDAF921FE06FE11" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="79" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31E8A0BFCDAF921FE06FE11" blockId="13.[835,1437,1455,1981]" lastBlockId="14.[151,752,207,401]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="79" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">
Two syntypes were cited by Kuntze for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FA80F921FBCBF975" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="polygamum" variety="thomae">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FA80F921FC5DF975" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Solanum polygamum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FBBAF940FB78F975" box="[1024,1249,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">thomae; Eggers 100</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FAA5F947FA0CF975" box="[1311,1429,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Kuntze 36</emphasis>
. Sheets of both of these were located at K; but the duplicate of 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FC0CF884FBB0F8B8" box="[950,1065,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Kuntze 36</emphasis>
at NY (
<figureCitation id="13412A3EB31E8A08FB33F885FB45F8B8" box="[1161,1244,1822,1848]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[151,185,1827,1848]" captionTargetBox="[204,1353,205,1804]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 4. a, lectotype of Solanum orthacanthum O.E. Schulz, Fuertes 1890 (A00077559). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University,Cambridge,Massachusetts,USA;b, lectotype of S. pachyneurum O.E.Schulz var.glabrescens O.E.Schulz,Wright 382 p.p.(left hand stems of GH00112906) (= S. pachyneuroides). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts, USA; c, lectotype of S. pachyneurum O.E. Schulz,Linden 1944 (K000196232). Reproduced with permission of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew; d, lectotype of S. polygamum Vahl var. thomae O. Kuntze, Kuntze 36 (NY0074477) (= S. polygamum). Reproduced with permission of the New York Botanical Garden." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326316/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
) is annotated by Kuntze and comes from his personal herbarium and is thus selected as the lectotype. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31E8A08FB24F8FAFC2EF81C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="inclusum" variety="albiflorum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FB24F8FAFAF5F8FB" box="[1182,1388,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">Solanum inclusum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31E8A08FCF9F819FC2EF81C" box="[835,951,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="78">albiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Eggers in his Flora of St. Croix and the Virgin Islands (1879) without citing a specimen or a specific locality, but is clearly a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31D8A0BFF40FF6BFE0FFE8A" box="[250,406,240,266]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polygamum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31D8A0BFF40FF6BFE0FFE8A" box="[250,406,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="79">S. polygamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The description is of a female plant 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31D8A0BFF66FE89FE1DFEAC" box="[220,388,274,300]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="79">
(
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31D8A0BFF5FFE89FE1DFEAC" box="[229,388,274,300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polygamum">S. polygamum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is dioecious, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B4AB31D8A0BFDEFFE89FF4BFECD" author="Knapp, S. &amp; Persson, V. &amp; Blackmore, S." journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="14" pageNumber="79" pagination="113 - 139" part="210" refId="ref14218" refString="Knapp, S., Persson, V. &amp; Blackmore, S. 1998. Pollen morphology and functional dioecy in Solanum (Solanaceae). Plant Systematics and Evolution 210: 113 - 139." title="Pollen morphology and functional dioecy in Solanum (Solanaceae)" type="journal article" year="1998">Knapp &amp; al., 1998</bibRefCitation>
), and I prefer to continue to search for fruiting material annotated by Eggers 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31D8A0BFE41FECEFD02FEEF" box="[507,667,341,367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polygamum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31D8A0BFE41FECEFD02FEEF" box="[507,667,341,367]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="79">S. polygamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
before neotypifying this name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
